From 2b293de0fa90b4e140ae0480914af2217dc6b2c8 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ramesh Mandal <ramesh@6epixels.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jul 2026 12:37:38 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat(m12): floating pill + live member cursors; fix the two
 remaining annotation bugs
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

THE TWO BUGS that kept pins/highlights dead (both now fixed):

1. socket.io's default first transport is HTTP long-polling, which uses
   XMLHttpRequest — XHR DOES NOT EXIST in MV3 service workers. The
   background relay could therefore never connect: every write timed
   out and returned 'offline' silently. transports:['websocket'] forces
   the one transport that works in every context we run in.

2. Clicking the 'Highlight this' button collapses the page's text
   selection on MOUSEDOWN — before the click handler runs — so
   serializeSelection() at click time read an empty selection and
   silently returned. The quote is now captured when the button is
   SHOWN (while the selection exists) and the button preventDefaults
   mousedown to keep the selection alive.

3. (Bonus, found during audit) communities were never in the zustand
   persist partialize — the content script's passive read path was
   reading a key the panel never wrote, and background-cached board
   data was wiped on the panel's next persist. Communities (which carry
   all board/pin/highlight data) and pillHidden now persist.

NEW — floating pill (per-community, enterprise-style opt-out):
- On-page pill (bottom-right, shadow DOM) appears when the user is a
  member of >=1 community with the pill enabled
- Expanded: community selector, Chat (opens the side panel via the
  documented user-gesture relay pattern), Add tab to board, Pin,
  Highlight, and a quick-message composer that posts to the community
  without opening the panel
- Toggle per community from the community's InfoPanel ('Disable/Enable
  floating pill on pages'), persisted

NEW — live member cursors (the multiplayer moment):
- Members of the same community on the SAME page (matched by
  canonicalKey) see each other's cursors: colored Figma-style arrow +
  name label, smoothly interpolated, throttled to ~11 updates/sec
- Ephemeral by design: relayed only, never stored (server test
  verifies member-only delivery + zero retention), cursors expire
  after 4s of silence, sharing stops on tab hide and resumes on return
- Background keeps its single connection alive while any tab is
  sharing; idle-disconnects 5s after the last one stops

Server: cursor_move/cursor_leave relay, membership-gated (28/28).
